  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am Nepali citizen havn Nepali pasport, want to travel to Dubai with my family from India, do v need nythng else apart frm pasport and visa?",
  "response": "As a Nepali citizen traveling to Dubai from India with your family, there are a few additional requirements and documents you may need apart from your **Nepali passport** and **Dubai visa**. Here's a checklist:\n\n### 1. **Valid Passport**\n   - Ensure your Nepali passports are valid for at least **6 months** from the date of entry into Dubai.\n\n### 2. **Dubai Visa**\n   - Obtain the appropriate visa for Dubai. Nepali citizens usually require a visa to enter the UAE. You can apply through the UAE embassy, a travel agency, or online platforms.\n\n### 3. **Flight Tickets**\n   - Have confirmed round-trip or onward flight tickets for all family members.\n\n### 4. **Accommodation Details**\n   - Proof of hotel booking or accommodation details in Dubai.\n\n### 5. **Travel Insurance** (Optional but Recommended)\n   - Travel insurance is not mandatory but highly recommended for medical emergencies and other unforeseen circumstances.\n\n### 6. **COVID-19 Requirements** (if applicable)\n   - Check the latest COVID-19 travel guidelines for Dubai, as they may change. This could include:\n     - Vaccination certificates\n     - Negative PCR test results (if required)\n     - Health declaration forms\n\n### 7. **Proof of Funds**\n   - Carry proof of sufficient funds for your stay in Dubai (bank statements, credit cards, cash, etc.).\n\n### 8. **Proof of Relationship** (if traveling with family)\n   - If you are traveling with family, carry documents like marriage certificates or birth certificates to prove relationships, especially if last names differ.\n\n### 9. **Exit Permit from India** (if applicable)\n   - If you are on a long-term visa or resident status in India, check if you need an **exit permit** to leave India.\n\n### 10. **Return to India Requirements**\n   - If you plan to return to India, ensure you have the necessary visa or permit to re-enter India (e.g., OCI card, Indian visa, etc.).\n\n### Tips:\n- Check the **latest UAE immigration guidelines** before traveling, as rules can change.\n- Ensure your visa type matches the purpose of your trip (e.g., tourist, visit, etc.).\n- If you have dual citizenship, carry both passports.\n\nIf you are unsure about any requirements, contact the **UAE Embassy** or your travel agent for clarification. Safe travels!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
